Kvapil doubts the thieves would be able to make any money off of the car.

'There's really no use for it out in the general public. I don't really know what you can do with it.' 

'I hope they realize that and will leave it somewhere where police can find it.'  

But even more than just the money, Kvapil told ESPN missing the race will hurt the team as the Sprint Cup series is determined by points per race.

'The beginning of the year, it's so important to establish yourself in the points, and they did a good job with a decent finish last week,' he said. 

'Missing this race will be a big setback for this little team.'   

